ehavior and first person contemplative applications to create a strictly secular and scientifically rigorous theoretical paradigm for investigating these questions programs summary of programs areas research objectives research projects education meng wu lecture series compassion cultivation training why cultivate compassion contributors to cct project compassion student group compassion in action user login username password create new account request new password 2012 compassion training course registration compassion training is a nine week course designed to develop the qualities of compassion empathy and kindness for oneself and for others two locations for winter courses stanford university and uc berkeley january 17 2012 through march 13 2012 click for more information spring course information coming soon volunteering for ccare if would like to be contacted about volunteer opportunities please click here 2011 the center for compassion and altruism research and education all rights reserved connect with us on make a gift
